fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of squares of roofing materials, measured in multiples of 100 square feet.

fields.name: strip
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of strips (strip: long narrow piece of an object).

fields.name: stick
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of sticks (stick: slender and often cylindrical piece of a substance).

fields.name: stick, cigarette
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of cigarettes in the smallest unit for stock-taking and/or duty computation.

fields.name: standard litre
fields.description: A unit of volume defining the number of litres of a product at a temperature of 15 degrees Celsius, especially in relation to hydrocarbon oils.

fields.name: ton (US) or short ton (UK/US)
fields.description: Synonym: net ton (2000 lb)

fields.name: straw
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of straws (straw: a slender tube used for sucking up liquids).

fields.name: skein
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of skeins (skein: a loosely-coiled bundle of yarn or thread).

fields.name: shipment
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of shipments (shipment: an amount of goods shipped or transported).

fields.name: syringe
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of syringes (syringe: a small device for pumping, spraying and/or injecting liquids through a small aperture).

fields.name: telecommunication line in service
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of lines in service.

fields.name: thousand piece
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of pieces in multiples of 1000 (piece: a single item, article or exemplar).

fields.name: total acid number
fields.description: A unit of chemistry defining the amount of potassium hydroxide (KOH) in milligrams that is needed to neutralize the acids in one gram of oil. It is an important quality measurement of crude oil.

fields.name: metric ton, including container
fields.description: A unit of mass defining the number of metric tons of a product, including its container.

fields.name: metric ton, including inner packaging
fields.description: A unit of mass defining the number of metric tons of a product, including its inner packaging materials.

fields.name: tonne kilometre
fields.description: A unit of information typically used for billing purposes, expressed as the number of tonnes (metric tons) moved over a distance of one kilometre.

fields.name: kilogram of imported meat, less offal
fields.description: A unit of mass equal to one thousand grams of imported meat, disregarding less valuable by-products such as the entrails.

fields.name: tonne (metric ton)
fields.description: Synonym: metric ton

fields.name: ten pack
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of items in multiples of 10.

fields.name: teeth per inch
fields.description: The number of teeth per inch.

fields.name: ten pair
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of pairs in multiples of 10 (pair: item described by two's).

fields.name: thousand cubic metre per day
fields.description: A unit of volume equal to one thousand cubic metres per day.

fields.name: ten set
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of sets in multiples of 10 (set: a number of objects grouped together).

fields.name: ten thousand sticks
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of sticks in multiples of 10000 (stick: slender and often cylindrical piece of a substance).

fields.name: treatment
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of treatments (treatment: subjection to the action of a chemical, physical or biological agent).

fields.name: tablet
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of tablets (tablet: a small flat or compressed solid object).

fields.name: telecommunication line in service average
fields.description: A unit of count defining the average number of lines in service.

fields.name: telecommunication port
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of network access ports.

fields.name: percent volume
fields.description: A measure of concentration, typically expressed as the percentage volume of a solute in a solution.

fields.name: wet kilo
fields.description: A unit of mass defining the number of kilograms of a product, including the water content of the product.

fields.name: wet pound
fields.description: A unit of mass defining the number of pounds of a material, including the water content of the material.

fields.name: cord
fields.description: A unit of volume used for measuring lumber. One board foot equals 1/12 of a cubic foot.

fields.name: wet ton
fields.description: A unit of mass defining the number of tons of a material, including the water content of the material.

fields.name: wine gallon
fields.description: A unit of volume equal to 231 cubic inches.

fields.name: working month
fields.description: A unit of time defining the number of working months.

fields.name: standard
fields.description: A unit of volume of finished lumber equal to 165 cubic feet. Synonym: standard cubic foot

fields.name: Gunter's chain
fields.description: A unit of distance used or formerly used by British surveyors.

fields.name: hanging container
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of hanging containers.

fields.name: page
fields.description: A unit of count defining the number of pages.

fields.name: mutually defined
fields.description: A unit of measure as agreed in common between two or more parties.
